Mercantile Bank said on Monday that South Africa‘s Capitec Bank, Nedbank Group and a consortium including the state pension fund had been shortlisted among its potential buyers. Mercantile said in a statement the Public Investment Corporation (PIC), Africa‘s largest asset manager, is leading a consortium seeking to buy the lender, which is owned by CGD, a Portuguese state-owned banking group. A total of 18 non-binding offers were received for Mercantile, which specialises in serving entrepreneurs, and the short-listed firms would conduct due diligence on the bank soon, the lender said.